ODE XXXIII.

‘Think not too much, Albius, of Glycera's faithlessness, nor write piteous elegies about your rejection. It is the way always. Lycoris pining sor Cyrus: Cyrus in love with Pholoe, who will as soon wed him as a she-goat a wolf. This is merely Venus' crue} sport. I am not exempt from the law!
